   "source": [
    "# Task 1: Statistical Foundations & Change Point Analysis\n",
    "Author: Hermona Addisu\n",
    "Objective: Establish statistical stationarity, analyze volatility clustering, and prepare for Bayesian structural break modeling."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Data Loading & Events Integration\n",
    "We load the historical Brent Oil prices and our curated dataset of 15 geopolitical shocks. The events dataset acts as our 'Ground Truth' for causal attribution later in the pipeline."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller\n",
    "\n",
    "prices = pd.read_csv('../data/BrentOilPrices.csv')\n",
    "prices['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(prices['Date'], format='mixed')\n",
    "prices = prices.sort_values('Date').reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "events = pd.read_csv('../data/external_events.csv')\n",
    "display(events.head())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Trend Analysis\n",
    "Visualizing the price history to identify global trends and periods of high variance."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
    "plt.plot(prices['Date'], prices['Price'])\n",
    "plt.title('Brent Oil Price History (1987-2022)')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('USD/Barrel')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Stationarity Testing (ADF)\n",
    "We use the Augmented Dickey-Fuller (ADF) test. If p-value > 0.05, the data is non-stationary, meaning we must model structural breaks to account for changing means."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "def check_stationarity(series):\n",
    "    res = adfuller(series)\n",
    "    print(f'ADF Statistic: {res[0]:.4f}')\n",
    "    print(f'p-value: {res[1]:.4e}')\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Testing Raw Prices:')\n",
    "check_stationarity(prices['Price'])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Volatility Analysis\n",
    "By calculating 21-day rolling standard deviation, we visualize 'Volatility Clustering' where periods of high risk tend to persist."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "prices['Log_Return'] = np.log(prices['Price'] / prices['Price'].shift(1))\n",
    "prices['Volatility'] = prices['Log_Return'].rolling(window=21).std() * (252**0.5)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 4))\n",
    "plt.plot(prices['Date'], prices['Volatility'], color='orange')\n",
    "plt.title('21-Day Annualized Rolling Volatility')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Bayesian Change Point Theory\n",
    "The goal is to detect a discrete shift in price regimes. We model the data as:\n",
    "- Regime 1: Mean $\\mu_1$ until time $\\tau$.\n",
    "- Regime 2: Mean $\\mu_2$ after time $\\tau$.\n",
    "We assign a Discrete Uniform Prior to $\\tau$, meaning any day could be the break date. We then use MCMC sampling to find the probability distribution of the true date."
   ]
  }
